@CHANGEME@ Project Description

## 🛠️ Build

This project is built with CMake presets. [kmpkg](https://github.com/kumose/kmcmake) is **optional** for dependency
management: when `KMPKG_CMAKE` is set, presets pick it up as `CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE`; when unset, the toolchain stays
empty and you can rely on system / manual dependencies.

### 0. Prepare the environment

- Linux (Ubuntu 20.04+ / CentOS 7+ Recommended) / macOS / Windows (MSVC + Ninja recommended)
- CMake >= 3.20
- GCC >= 9.4 / Clang >= 12 / MSVC (VS 2022+)
- Optional: install `kmpkg` — see [installation guide](https://kumo-pub.github.io/docs/category/%E6%8C%81%E7%BB%AD%E9%9B%86%E6%88%90----kmpkg)
- Optional: `ninja` on PATH when using `--preset=ninja`

### 1.Configure the project (optional, kmpkg)

* For the complete dependencies, refer to [`kmpkg.json`](kmpkg.json)
* To update the dependency baseline, modify the `baseline` in `default-registry` of [`kmpkg-configuration.json`](kmpkg-configuration.json)
* the `baseline` can be obtained via `git log`.


### 2. Build the project

Run in the project root directory:

```bash
# Unix Makefiles (default) → build/
cmake --preset=default
cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

# Ninja → build-ninja/  (install ninja first)
cmake --preset=ninja
cmake --build build-ninja -j$(nproc)
```

#### Using Manual Dependency Management

If you manage dependencies yourself (no kmpkg), leave `KMPKG_CMAKE` unset and use the same presets, or plain CMake:

```shell
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
make -j$(nproc)
```

**Note**

- Presets `default` and `ninja` are defined in `CMakePresets.json` at the project root.
- When managing dependencies manually, make sure CMake’s find_package can locate all required libraries.

### 3. Run Tests (Optional)

Run in the project root directory:

```shell
ctest --test-dir build
# or, if you used the ninja preset:
ctest --test-dir build-ninja
```
